1. Current Manual Process
Today, when we want to hit an on-prem API via AWS, we need to create a reverse proxy in Apigee (APG).
While creating this reverse proxy, we must select an authentication method. APG supports two:
Okta
APG Auth
Our automation applies to the APG Auth method.
Once the reverse proxy and its respective APG product are created:
The developer has to go to the APG DIY application.
Add the proxy inside that application.
Enter their own credentials.
Then APG DIY generates a Client ID and Client Secret.
The user copies these values and manually pastes them into AWS Secrets Manager.
AWS Secrets Manager is then used for authentication in the overall flow.
